A burst of flames shot from Thassalin's jaws as the colossal Thraki incinerated a precise section of the forest, then circled above, observing it for a time. Strangely, as he had slowed down, the odd sounds of screams behind him had stopped. Thassalin forgot that he had passengers on his back.
"Come on, Tenuk, you've already transformed into Thraki before!"
"My flight is very different. I am not suddenly lifted by a huge pink dragon!"
"Isn't it not so unpleasant, Kayel?"
Kayel clearly wasn't agreeing with Nyssi; he seemed less angry than usual and had dug his claws into Thassalin's back, causing the Thraki to bleed, but obviously, he didn't care much about it. Still, Thassalin realized he had terrified his new friends and found a clearing where to land.
"MY APologies, I SMELLED A SCENT. I HAD TO CHECK."
"Did you have to drag us here with you?" Tenuk launched, sliding down from Thassalin's back along its tail. "And we left Retvik behind! We abandoned our great and strong fighter! How is he going to catch up with us?"
"She'll find a way," retorted Nyssi. "Retvik is slow, but not stupid."
"Okay, but does Retvik know how to drive?"
Nyssi blinked and turned towards Tenuk. "Of course he knows how to drive."
"Have you ever seen Retvik driving a vehicle? He doesn't have a truck like yours, and I've never seen him drive something as cute as Kayel's little car either, and if he started coming to work by car, it's only because YOU took us. He just has this bike."
A burst of laughter interrupted them. Thassalin was suddenly hysterical, and no one understood what had made him laugh. It took him a bit too long to calm down.
"SORRY, BUT I IMAGINED YOUR BIG FRIEND IN ARMOR ON A MINIATURE BICYCLE DESIGNED FOR CHILDREN TEMTHAN. IT WAS SO FUNNY! I WISH I HAD TELEPATHY. THAT'S A VALUABLE THOUGHT! ONE I CAN'T SHARE!"
Kayel chuckled, imagining what Thassalin must have been thinking. "Yes, that's right. But what did you pick up, and why did you take off so quickly?"
Thassalin growled, took off, and briefly disappeared before returning and dropping a carcass in front of Nyssi. It was an Orothrack, a rare golden and white dragon-like creature. But its head was missing. "ANOTHER DEATH. I HEAR THEIR CRIES. I FEEL THEIR BLOOD. I AM PROGRAMMED TO PROTECT AND HUNT. AS YISINI DEMANDS. CREATURES ARE NEAR."
The powerful Thraki suddenly froze. So did Nyssi and Kayel, their attention drawn by a gap in the clearing. Something large and black was staring at them, hissing. Whatever it was, this thing spread two colossal pairs of wings and charged straight at Thassalin, paying no mind to the three smaller beings in its path. Kayel and Tenuk managed to take cover barely in time, but Nyssi was dragged along and nearly thrown onto Thassalin.
Thassalin reacted to the aggression by catching Nyssi and throwing her onto his back using his extraordinary long and dexterous tail, before taking off. The two-winged black creature rushed quickly after them.
Kayel sighed, drawing the rifle from his back, then opened a pouch containing a belt of ammunition. He slung it over his shoulder for easy access, but quickly realized that Nyssi, the Thraki, and the monster were no longer visible.
"Hé Tenuk, would you like to transform into something that flies?" asked Kayel.
"Do you want to chase them?"
"Yes, of course!"
"But... one of them is a giant monster!"
"And then what? I have a super powerful rifle in my hands right now, ready to serve. I just need to see it to shoot at it."
Tenuk hesitated, then stepped back to give himself some space. With a faint growl slightly embarrassed, his body unfolded, his fur was replaced by scales, and his arms transformed into wings. He quickly reverted to the usual light blue Thraki, but his eyes remained red.
"Climb."
Having returned to a more normal Thraki appearance, Tenuk now had a back covered in scales, but a pair of spikes had also grown there, practical for Kayel to grip onto. Tenuk needed a bit of time to take off, but once in the air, he quickly oriented himself and tried to pursue.
However, Tenuk and Kayel realized quickly that they were not alone. A second dark creature emerged from below, and Tenuk managed to avoid it barely.
I suppose it's the other big scary monster that was worrying Lanex? Kayel frowned as he tried to aim at the second beastie, missed his target, and quickly reloaded his weapon.
Tenuk did not react. He was too focused on his flight towards Nyssi and Thassalin, despite the other creature pursuing them. Kayel awkwardly spun around, facing the monster. The fact that it was chasing them was an advantage for Kayel, as it made it easier for him to aim and shoot. Two shots passed through the creature's upper wings, which screamed in pain as it disappeared again under the trees. Kayel did not know if it was still following them, but she would certainly not be able to catch up.
Further away, Nyssi clung desperately, while Thassalin flew in circles, launching bursts of flames at the blackened monster. Although the creature was clearly injured, it seemed furious and determined to fight, and the fireballs did not seem to have the desired effect. When Thassalin straightened, Nyssi took the opportunity to draw her weapon, a reliable rifle. Of course, it was not designed for this kind of situation, but a burst of shots would surely at least deter the black beast?
